# Velocity Temlate Launguage (VTL)

## Use Guide Contents:  https://velocity.apache.org/engine/1.7/user-guide.html#references

## https://velocity.apache.org/engine/1.7/user-guide.html#hello-velocity-world

## References:  
-----------
There are three types of references in the VTL:

## Variables: = $ followed by (a..z, A..Z) - the rest can be any of these: (a..z,A..Z), (0..9), ("-"), ("_")
## Examples:  $foo  $mudSlinger, $mud-slinger, $mud_slinger, $mudslinger3

## Properties: =$ followed a VTL Identifier, followed by a dot character (".") and another VTL Identifier. 
	
## Examples:  $customer.Address, $purchase.Total

## Methods
## Directive: #set( $foo = "bar" )
